<doc id="332114" wikidata="Q1367145" url="?curid=332114" title="Chechen naxar">
<text>The naxar (, co-spelled &quot;nakhar&quot; or &quot;nahar&quot;) is the currency that Chechen separatists planned for the Chechen Republic of Ichkeria.

In 1994, in the UK, banknotes were printed in denominations of 1, 3, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100, 500, and 1000 nakhar, dated 1995.

This currency was not put into circulation, and almost all printed banknotes stored in bank of Grozny were destroyed by the Russian military.

The name is derived from the Chechen нахарт (&quot;nakhart&quot;), meaning &quot;small change.&quot;

